get blog permalink "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==================================================================

NAME
----

get blog permalink - Get the permalink for a blog post from any site on the network.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Get the permalink for a blog post from any site on the network.

USAGE
-----

`  <?php echo get_blog_permalink( $blog_id, $post_id ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$blog_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) ID of the blog.
    Default: *None*

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) ID of the post you are looking for.
    Default: *None*

EXAMPLE
-------

From any blog in the network, get the permalink for post with ID 6 on
blog ID 3. `  <?php echo get_blog_permalink( 3, 6 ); ?> `

RETURNS
-------

 (string) 
:   The permalink URL.

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_blog_permalink()` is located in `wp-includes/ms-functions.php`.

